{% layout "layouts/base.liquid" %}
{% block title %}Tabs — Cubito UI Docs{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<article class="flow">

  <header class="padding-y-m margin-y-m" style="border-block-end: 1px solid var(--color-neutral-200);">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="breadcrumb">
      <ol>
        <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="/components/">Components</a></li>
        <li aria-current="page">Tabs</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>
    <h1>Tabs</h1>
    <p class="text-l color-neutral-600">A WAI-ARIA compliant tabbed interface with three visual variants: default underline, pills, and lifted card-style tabs.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="callout" data-variant="brand" role="note">
    <p>JavaScript is required to manage <code>aria-selected</code>, <code>tabindex</code>, and panel visibility. The script at the bottom of this page powers all three demos. In production, consider adding keyboard arrow-key navigation as described in the <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/tabs/">WAI-ARIA Tabs pattern</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <section>
    <h2 class="heading-l">Default</h2>
    <p>The default variant uses an underline indicator on the selected tab. The tablist has a bottom border that the indicator sits on top of.</p>
    
    <div class="padding-m margin-y-m background-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200">
<div class="tabs">
  <div role="tablist" aria-label="Product details">
    <button role="tab" id="tab-desc" aria-controls="panel-desc" aria-selected="true">Description</button>
    <button role="tab" id="tab-specs" aria-controls="panel-specs" aria-selected="false" tabindex="-1">Specifications</button>
    <button role="tab" id="tab-reviews" aria-controls="panel-reviews" aria-selected="false" tabindex="-1">Reviews</button>
  </div>

  <div role="tabpanel" id="panel-desc" aria-labelledby="tab-desc">
    <p>The Meridian Backpack is built for the daily commute and weekend adventures alike. Its water-resistant outer shell and padded 15&Prime; laptop sleeve keep your gear protected whatever the weather.</p>
  </div>
  <div role="tabpanel" id="panel-specs" aria-labelledby="tab-specs" hidden>
    <p>Capacity: 28 L — Dimensions: 48 × 32 × 18 cm — Weight: 890 g — Material: 600D recycled polyester.</p>
  </div>
  <div role="tabpanel" id="panel-reviews" aria-labelledby="tab-reviews" hidden>
    <p>Rated 4.7 out of 5 from 312 verified purchases. Customers praise the build quality and comfortable shoulder straps.</p>
  </div>
</div>
    </div>

    <details class="margin-y-s">
      <summary class="padding-s">Show code</summary>
      <pre class="padding-m background-neutral-900" style="overflow-x: auto;"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;tabs&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div role=&quot;tablist&quot; aria-label=&quot;Product details&quot;&gt;
    &lt;button role=&quot;tab&quot; id=&quot;tab-desc&quot; aria-controls=&quot;panel-desc&quot; aria-selected=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Description&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button role=&quot;tab&quot; id=&quot;tab-specs&quot; aria-controls=&quot;panel-specs&quot; aria-selected=&quot;false&quot; tabindex=&quot;-1&quot;&gt;Specifications&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button role=&quot;tab&quot; id=&quot;tab-reviews&quot; aria-controls=&quot;panel-reviews&quot; aria-selected=&quot;false&quot; tabindex=&quot;-1&quot;&gt;Reviews&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div role=&quot;tabpanel&quot; id=&quot;panel-desc&quot; aria-labelledby=&quot;tab-desc&quot;&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;The Meridian Backpack is built for the daily commute and weekend adventures alike. Its water-resistant outer shell and padded 15&amp;Prime; laptop sleeve keep your gear protected whatever the weather.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div role=&quot;tabpanel&quot; id=&quot;panel-specs&quot; aria-labelledby=&quot;tab-specs&quot; hidden&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Capacity: 28 L — Dimensions: 48 × 32 × 18 cm — Weight: 890 g — Material: 600D recycled polyester.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div role=&quot;tabpanel&quot; id=&quot;panel-reviews&quot; aria-labelledby=&quot;tab-reviews&quot; hidden&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Rated 4.7 out of 5 from 312 verified purchases. Customers praise the build quality and comfortable shoulder straps.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
    </details>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="heading-l">Pills variant</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-variant="pills"</code> to the <code>.tabs</code> wrapper. The tablist gains a neutral background pill and the active tab is raised with a white background and a subtle shadow.</p>
    
    <div class="padding-m margin-y-m background-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200">
<div class="tabs" data-variant="pills">
  <div role="tablist" aria-label="Account settings">
    <button role="tab" id="tab2-profile" aria-controls="panel2-profile" aria-selected="true">Profile</button>
    <button role="tab" id="tab2-billing" aria-controls="panel2-billing" aria-selected="false" tabindex="-1">Billing</button>
    <button role="tab" id="tab2-security" aria-controls="panel2-security" aria-selected="false" tabindex="-1">Security</button>
  </div>

  <div role="tabpanel" id="panel2-profile" aria-labelledby="tab2-profile">
    <p>Update your display name, email address, and avatar from the profile settings panel.</p>
  </div>
  <div role="tabpanel" id="panel2-billing" aria-labelledby="tab2-billing" hidden>
    <p>Manage your subscription plan, view invoices, and update your payment method.</p>
  </div>
  <div role="tabpanel" id="panel2-security" aria-labelledby="tab2-security" hidden>
    <p>Change your password, enable two-factor authentication, and review active sessions.</p>
  </div>
</div>
    </div>

    <details class="margin-y-s">
      <summary class="padding-s">Show code</summary>
